## Photoresistor

The photoresistor is used in order to start the robot's autonimous operation. It will detect the light emitted from the starting LED and use that signal to begin
the robot's operation. This will meet specifications 2 and 5.

Purpose and Justification:
The photoresistor is used to autonomously start the robot, which is a critical function in order for the robot to operate successfully.
The robot's ability to start autonomously will secure the team a total of 15 points during the competition, and allow the robot to complete other task to score
more points.
This test is to ensure that the photoresistor will be able to reliably start the robot, using the starting LED.

Detailed Procedure:

The robot uses a single photoresistor that is located at its rear. It is connected from 3.3 V power to the robot's Arduino Mega. As the photoresistor is
exposed to more light, the analog value that is recorded by the Ardunio decreases as the photoresistor's resistance increases. The Arduino will dectect the starting
LED if the analog value of the photoresister is under a predefined threshold, at which the robot will being to move forward. A successful test is defined by the robot
moving forward after being exposed to the starting LED.

